  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 490 mg
time required: 45 minutes
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cranberry-dijon-chicken-6759e7a1fa9f4da845f64703
---

Adjust rack to middle position (middle and top positions for 4 servings) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb} until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4). Pick @rosemary{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; mince leaves until you have 1 tsp.

Place potatoes in a medium #pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve 1⁄2 cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot. Mash with @sour cream{3%tablespoon} and @butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) using a #potato masher{} until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While potatoes cook, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with salt and pepper.

> Swap in pork filet for chicken. Cook until browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Toss Brussels sprouts in a large #bowl{} with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper. Spread out on one side of a #baking sheet{}. Roast ~{5%minutes}.

Add chicken to empty side of sheet. Add @lemon zest{} to Brussels sprouts with @lemon{1}(zested). For 4 servings, toss Brussels sprouts on a second sheet; roast pork on middle rack and Brussels sprouts on top rack.

Roast on middle rack until chicken is cooked through and Brussels sprouts are tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Carefully toss Brussels sprouts with lemon zest.

> Skip roasting chicken; spread Brussels sprouts across entire sheet.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add minced ginger and minced rosemary; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @cranberry jam{1}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, and @water{1/4%cup} (1/3 cup for 4 servings). Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat; stir in @butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted.

Slice chicken crosswise.

> Slice pork crosswise if using pork.

Divide chicken, mashed potatoes, and Brussels sprouts between #plates{}. Drizzle chicken with sauce. Serve with lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.